    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-04-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-04-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="22"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d22">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.689 Liquor/5</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Greek Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Simopoulos</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 3, 1928</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 540</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>The Minister of Greece presents his compliments to His Excellency The Secretary
                    of State and has the honor to acknowledge the receipt of the Department’s Note
                    No. 711.689/3, dated March 22, 1928, concerning the conclusion of a convention
                    pertaining to alcoholic beverages on board ships flying the Greek flag.</p>
                <p>The Minister of Greece is pleased to inform His Excellency The Secretary of State
                    that the draft of the convention, so kindly forwarded to this Legation, has been
                    given due consideration, and that he has been duly authorized to sign it.</p>
                <p>The Minister of Greece has the honor to forward to His Excellency The Secretary
                    of State the instrument by which full power is given to him<note n="17"
                        xml:id="d22fn17">Not printed.</note> to sign this convention.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
